writeLines(c("# ECI And PCI Technical Validation","","ECI is recomputed year by year from the binary RCA matrix using the country-side normalized reflection matrix `D_c^-1 M D_p^-1 M'`. The second eigenvector is selected, standardized within year, and sign-oriented to correlate positively with diversity.","","PCI is a projected product index: product values are obtained by projecting country ECI through the product side of the RCA matrix and standardizing within year. It is not a separate product-side eigen-decomposition.","","Because ECI and PCI are standardized separately each year, they support relative within-year comparisons and rankings. Changes over time should be interpreted as changes in relative position, not absolute capability accumulation.","",paste0("Max absolute annual ECI mean: ",signif(max(abs(eci_val$mean_eci)),3)),paste0("Annual ECI sd range: ",round(min(eci_val$sd_eci),3),"-",round(max(eci_val$sd_eci),3)),paste0("Annual PCI sd range: ",round(min(pci_val$sd_pci),3),"-",round(max(pci_val$sd_pci),3))), p("docs/ECI_PCI_TECHNICAL_VALIDATION.md"), useBytes=TRUE)
